00:01:15.530 --> 00:01:20.630
Officer for Volkswagen of
Nigeria, and in academia.

00:01:20.630 --> 00:01:23.870
He is the author of several
management and public policy

00:01:23.870 --> 00:01:27.240
books, including
the award-winning

00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:30.300
"Managing Uncertainty,
Competition and Strategy

00:01:30.300 --> 00:01:36.630
in Emerging Economies" in 1998,
and the 2006 book "Why Nations

00:01:36.630 --> 00:01:37.440
Are Poor."

00:01:37.440 --> 00:01:39.410
He has been a
scholar in residence

00:01:39.410 --> 00:01:42.190
at the Harvard Business
School and the American

00:01:42.190 --> 00:01:45.100
University in Washington DC.

00:01:45.100 --> 00:01:48.490
As leader of civil
society, he is the founder

00:01:48.490 --> 00:01:52.540
of the Center for Values in
Leadership, the Widow Support

00:01:52.540 --> 00:01:56.340
Centre, and the Concerned
Professionals, which

00:01:56.340 --> 00:01:59.380
was bulwark against
military operation

00:01:59.380 --> 00:02:03.280
among numerous other social
enterprise initiatives,

00:02:03.280 --> 00:02:05.630
and honored by so many
professional bodies

00:02:05.630 --> 00:02:09.130
for the collection of
more than 700 plaques

00:02:09.130 --> 00:02:10.773
that mark a life of service.

