commercial banks

00:44:41.760 --> 00:44:42.810
in the country.

00:44:42.810 --> 00:44:46.650
And he says to me, oh, Pat,
what a fantastic-- he goes on

00:44:46.650 --> 00:44:47.582
and on and on.

00:44:47.582 --> 00:44:49.540
When he finished, I said
to him, you know what?

00:44:49.540 --> 00:44:52.220
I'm glad you love it, because
we need commercial support

00:44:52.220 --> 00:44:53.775
for that thing to be air.

00:44:53.775 --> 00:44:56.880
He said, oh, Pat, but you guys
speak the truth, you know.

00:44:56.880 --> 00:44:58.265
And truth is not--

00:44:58.265 --> 00:44:59.356
JULIET EHIMUAN: Lucrative.

00:44:59.356 --> 00:45:01.230
PAT UTOMI: You know, I
wouldn't want somebody

00:45:01.230 --> 00:45:04.582
to think that I'm putting
you guys up to that speaking

00:45:04.582 --> 00:45:06.927
of the truth, you know?

00:45:06.927 --> 00:45:08.760
But the day you will
do sports, let me know.

00:45:08.760 --> 00:45:11.270
We'll pay twice as much.

00:45:11.270 --> 00:45:13.380
But that was part
of the problem.

00:45:13.380 --> 00:45:15.510
Actually, the reason
I could keep that

00:45:15.510 --> 00:45:17.946
show running for
as long as I did--

00:45:17.946 --> 00:45:19.620
it was more than 10 years.

00:45:19.620 --> 00:45:23.200
It did come back after
a one-year break.

00:45:23.200 --> 00:45:28.930
It was on until last year,
second quarter of last year,

00:45:28.930 --> 00:45:32.140
but when it first started,
it was on the NTA network.

00:45:32.140 --> 00:45:33.120
It was on channels.

00:45:33.120 --> 00:45:36.450
It was literally on
every television at work.

00:45:36.450 --> 00:45:40.570
And not only did we spend a
lot of money to produce it,

00:45:40.570 --> 00:45:44.280
we paid those television
stations to air it.

00:45:44.280 --> 00:45:46.590
That's the kind of
business model we have.

00:45:46.590 --> 00:45:51.580
Instead of them to pay you
for content, you paid to air.

00:45:51.580 --> 00:45:55.340
And the way that [INAUDIBLE]
television going was we

00:45:55.340 --> 00:45:58.320
had-- the computer was set off.

00:45:58.320 --> 00:46:04.710
Had a big institutional
advertising contract

00:46:04.710 --> 00:46:09.030
with a big multinational, and
something completely different

00:46:09.030 --> 00:46:12.520
that was called
leadership reflections.

00:46:12.520 --> 00:46:15.430
But they paid us so well
that the entire gain

00:46:15.430 --> 00:46:17.560
from that, and more,
we had to fight

00:46:17.560 --> 00:46:21.850
for-- went into that program--
was one particular year,

00:46:21.850 --> 00:46:25.235
it cost me literally
100 million naira

00:46:25.235 --> 00:46:28.890
to keep "Patito's
Gang" on the air.

00:46:28.890 --> 00:46:31.190
Advertising revenue,
Nigerian companies

00:46:31.190 --> 00:46:35.136
were scared to advertise on
a program that spoke truth

00:46:35.136 --> 00:46:37.100
to power.

00:46:37.100 --> 00:46:42.280
So you see how challenging
it can be out there.

00:46:42.280 --> 00:46:44.470
So after many years, I
have become literally

00:46:44.470 --> 00:46:48.560
bankrupt from trying to do
service to the Nigerian people.

00:46:48.560 --> 00:46:50.120
And I thought, I
better stop this.

00:46:50.120 --> 00:46:52.510
And as soon as I stopped,
everybody started complaining.

00:46:52.510 --> 00:46:54.270
So we had to try and get back.

00:46:54.270 --> 00:46:56.320
But yes, I'd be pleased
to do another one.

