00:49:16.988 --> 00:49:18.710
You are developing
other economies

00:49:18.710 --> 00:49:23.610
and starving your own country of
oxygen. And maybe I'm foolish,

00:49:23.610 --> 00:49:28.916
but I don't have much-- I tell
people I don't have a room.

00:49:28.916 --> 00:49:30.522
Most people have several houses.

00:49:30.522 --> 00:49:31.230
I was in Nigeria.

00:49:31.230 --> 00:49:33.779
I don't have a room
outside Nigeria.

00:49:33.779 --> 00:49:35.820
Almost every investment,
just about-- not almost.

00:49:35.820 --> 00:49:38.680
Every investment I
have is in Nigeria.

00:49:38.680 --> 00:49:43.760
I probably can find 20,000
pounds or something that I

00:49:43.760 --> 00:49:46.420
leave abroad just
in case I can't send

00:49:46.420 --> 00:49:48.740
my childrens' [INAUDIBLE]
quickly enough from Nigerian

00:49:48.740 --> 00:49:50.202
banks.

00:49:50.202 --> 00:49:51.910
But I would never
probably have much more

00:49:51.910 --> 00:49:54.870
than that outside Nigeria.

00:49:54.870 --> 00:49:56.620
For people who are
not particular wise,

00:49:56.620 --> 00:50:01.040
it might seem like something
prestigious, or something

00:50:01.040 --> 00:50:03.080
that they play safe with.

00:50:03.080 --> 00:50:04.540
But you know what happens?

00:50:04.540 --> 00:50:08.990
Most of them, most of them
die and leave all that money.

00:50:08.990 --> 00:50:11.230
Because there are usually
not man enough to even

00:50:11.230 --> 00:50:15.470
tell their wives that
they have such money.

00:50:15.470 --> 00:50:17.495
So it is not wisdom,
it's foolishness.

00:50:23.745 --> 00:50:25.120
That is said very
often, but it's

00:50:25.120 --> 00:50:29.620
one of those lies that the
system structures to, you know,

00:50:29.620 --> 00:50:30.850
let people feed on.

00:50:30.850 --> 00:50:33.410
First of all, the Senate is a
completely useless institution.

00:50:33.410 --> 00:50:36.230
It has no power whatsoever,
affects nothing,

00:50:36.230 --> 00:50:37.230
as far as I'm concerned.

00:50:37.230 --> 00:50:40.210
Except the [INAUDIBLE].

00:50:40.210 --> 00:50:43.150
If we need to
restructure government,

00:50:43.150 --> 00:50:47.760
I would go to a unicameral
legislature that is very small.

00:50:47.760 --> 00:50:50.810
[INAUDIBLE], who is
currently a minister,

00:50:50.810 --> 00:50:54.790
after serving in the Senate,
when I was running in 2006,

00:50:54.790 --> 00:51:00.274
said to me, you know, the
years I spent in the Senate

00:51:00.274 --> 00:51:01.690
were the biggest
waste of my life.

00:51:04.372 --> 00:51:08.910
They do very little
in terms of value add.

00:51:08.910 --> 00:51:10.510
It's culture.

00:51:10.510 --> 00:51:13.280
It's a culture of executive.

00:51:13.280 --> 00:51:14.620
You have the strings.

00:51:14.620 --> 00:51:16.910
Because all people
are looking for

00:51:16.910 --> 00:51:19.590
is the purse who can
hold the purse strings.

00:51:19.590 --> 00:51:22.630
Everybody comes
bowing before you.

00:51:22.630 --> 00:51:26.820
And not knowing that you can use
the instruments to do greater

00:51:26.820 --> 00:51:29.370
good, they focus
on the power side.

00:51:29.370 --> 00:51:33.140
So I really don't believe
in the legislature thing.

00:51:33.140 --> 00:51:35.634
It can be wonderful,
legislature.

00:51:35.634 --> 00:51:37.050
But the way it's
structured today,

00:51:37.050 --> 00:51:38.480
you contribute freely to it.

00:51:38.480 --> 00:51:44.430
If we return to a elementary
British, Westminster type

00:51:44.430 --> 00:51:49.310
system, then I would
value the legislature.

00:51:49.310 --> 00:51:52.410
Right now, really the
only thing that matters

00:51:52.410 --> 00:51:54.920
is the executive branch.

00:51:54.920 --> 00:51:57.040
Judiciary can be very important.

00:51:57.040 --> 00:51:59.080
They do certain things
to help the building

00:51:59.080 --> 00:52:00.672
of the institutions.

00:52:00.672 --> 00:52:01.630
But you know the track.

00:52:01.630 --> 00:52:05.220
There is a different track.

00:52:05.220 --> 00:52:09.090
The other part of
the question is

00:52:09.090 --> 00:52:16.220
about what I think of the
way things are right now.

00:52:16.220 --> 00:52:18.850
I think that what has affected
the way things are right now,

00:52:18.850 --> 00:52:26.490
same reason why the [INAUDIBLE]
who ran-- how did we get here?

00:52:26.490 --> 00:52:30.155
Again, history often does not
get written fairly or properly.

00:52:32.880 --> 00:52:36.050
From my experience
in 2007, I was

00:52:36.050 --> 00:52:41.060
convinced that if Nigeria did
not build a viable opposition,

00:52:41.060 --> 00:52:44.070
Nigeria was not going
to get very far.

00:52:44.070 --> 00:52:48.130
If power does not go
from one group in power

00:52:48.130 --> 00:52:51.870
today to another-- their
position nobody feeds

00:52:51.870 --> 00:52:57.124
the incumbent regime,
democracy will not

00:52:57.124 --> 00:52:58.332
be different in this country.

00:52:58.332 --> 00:53:01.090
And so my commitment
from the beginning

00:53:01.090 --> 00:53:05.220
was in working with
an opposition group

00:53:05.220 --> 00:53:08.290
to build a true opposition.

00:53:08.290 --> 00:53:11.160
In post-colonial Africa,
there's a concept

00:53:11.160 --> 00:53:15.290
of the corporatist state, where
the state tries to incorporate

00:53:15.290 --> 00:53:17.632
a strong voice of opposition.

00:53:17.632 --> 00:53:20.750
You get appointed a
minister by people

00:53:20.750 --> 00:53:24.990
who don't like you so that
they can keep you quiet.

00:53:24.990 --> 00:53:26.480
[INAUDIBLE] in Africa.

00:53:26.480 --> 00:53:30.085
At some point in
time, [INAUDIBLE]

00:53:30.085 --> 00:53:31.460
to become an
attorney general was

00:53:31.460 --> 00:53:33.675
becoming president of the
Nigerian Bar Association.

00:53:33.675 --> 00:53:36.050
Because the Bar Association
used to give a lot of trouble

00:53:36.050 --> 00:53:36.730
to government.

00:53:36.730 --> 00:53:39.850
[INAUDIBLE] becoming
Minister of Health

00:53:39.850 --> 00:53:43.930
was President of the
Nigerian Medical Association.

00:53:43.930 --> 00:53:48.826
As an example I like to
give-- [INAUDIBLE] to him--

00:53:48.826 --> 00:53:53.270
a very strong leader of
the enemy [INAUDIBLE]

00:53:53.270 --> 00:53:56.280
became minister of health,
and the government usually

00:53:56.280 --> 00:53:58.890
used him to destroy the enemy.

00:53:58.890 --> 00:54:01.240
And the day he was
dropped from the cabinet,

00:54:01.240 --> 00:54:04.430
a person close to him
said he cried like a baby.

00:54:04.430 --> 00:54:07.040
He had nowhere to go back
to, and nobody has ever

00:54:07.040 --> 00:54:10.720
since heard of him.

00:54:10.720 --> 00:54:12.705
So many times that
I've been asked

00:54:12.705 --> 00:54:17.110
to cabinet positions, questions
that I've always asked

00:54:17.110 --> 00:54:18.500
is, to do what?

00:54:18.500 --> 00:54:22.225
If you want me in a team, I
want a certain critical mass

00:54:22.225 --> 00:54:25.010
of people who
believe in something.

00:54:25.010 --> 00:54:26.910
And you must believe
in a certain agenda

00:54:26.910 --> 00:54:31.620
that we all agree to
before the journey starts.

00:54:31.620 --> 00:54:35.730
So what you do see happening
is going on right now,

00:54:35.730 --> 00:54:41.730
is that I think we have
a team that isn't even

00:54:41.730 --> 00:54:43.444
[INAUDIBLE] the
person who's leading.

00:54:46.147 --> 00:54:47.980
I think that most
ambassadors of the cabinet

00:54:47.980 --> 00:54:50.410
will tell you that they don't
agree with the policies that

00:54:50.410 --> 00:54:52.212
have left these petrol queues.

