They will tell you
they don't agree

00:54:53.670 --> 00:54:56.090
with the policies that
have created a mess

00:54:56.090 --> 00:54:57.940
in the foreign exchange market.

00:54:57.940 --> 00:55:03.650
They will tell you they don't
agree with the policies that

00:55:03.650 --> 00:55:07.780
are affecting, very
sadly, [INAUDIBLE]

00:55:07.780 --> 00:55:11.410
of educational system
and so on and so forth.

00:55:11.410 --> 00:55:13.360
But everybody is
looking ineffectual,

00:55:13.360 --> 00:55:16.980
because people haven't
developed the culture

00:55:16.980 --> 00:55:23.240
of saying "I'm sorry, this is
not what we agreed, I quit."

00:55:23.240 --> 00:55:25.020
But I think that
that is very useful,

00:55:25.020 --> 00:55:31.370
to send a signal to
people who have authority.

00:55:31.370 --> 00:55:35.017
JULIET EHIMUAN: Well,
thank you very much, Prof.

00:55:35.017 --> 00:55:36.350
I know there are many questions.

00:55:36.350 --> 00:55:38.290
I do apologize.

00:55:38.290 --> 00:55:40.210
I also have a lot
of questions, but we

00:55:40.210 --> 00:55:44.313
can't get to them, because Prof
has a lecture this afternoon.

00:55:44.313 --> 00:55:46.830
So we have to wrap up.

00:55:46.830 --> 00:55:49.428
But we can continue the
conversation online.

00:55:49.428 --> 00:55:51.136
To wrap up, I'm just
going to ask, what's

00:55:51.136 --> 00:55:53.280
the next chapter for you?

00:55:53.280 --> 00:55:55.940
What do the next
60 years look like?

00:55:55.940 --> 00:56:00.090
PAT UTOMI: Oh, this is going to
sound a little corny, because I

00:56:00.090 --> 00:56:01.710
keep telling people--
young people,

00:56:01.710 --> 00:56:04.840
and it's the truth--
from very early,

00:56:04.840 --> 00:56:07.310
I had the good fortune of
re-instituting [INAUDIBLE]

00:56:07.310 --> 00:56:09.040
very early in my life.

00:56:09.040 --> 00:56:11.730
And so I had a vision statement.

00:56:11.730 --> 00:56:14.280
I had personal missions.

00:56:14.280 --> 00:56:16.960
I had all of those things.

00:56:16.960 --> 00:56:22.150
But I tell you, it's important
to live it one day at a time.

00:56:22.150 --> 00:56:25.380
However, I think that, as
I keep making this point,

00:56:25.380 --> 00:56:31.090
that Nigeria has a major
public life challenge, that

00:56:31.090 --> 00:56:34.620
is going to take
individual effort to move

00:56:34.620 --> 00:56:37.170
Nigeria towards its destiny.

00:56:37.170 --> 00:56:40.790
I'm looking to play
private roles that

00:56:40.790 --> 00:56:45.830
can have transformative
impact in the economy.

00:56:45.830 --> 00:56:48.620
I look at Nigeria
at a time when,

00:56:48.620 --> 00:56:53.080
given its general endowments--
human, particularly--

00:56:53.080 --> 00:56:58.615
and the possibilities in Africa
seen from the era of Afro

00:56:58.615 --> 00:57:02.232
pessimism to one in which
significant progress is

00:57:02.232 --> 00:57:07.240
expected, that private capital
can come into this country

00:57:07.240 --> 00:57:11.560
from elsewhere, if we can
manage to do enough talking

00:57:11.560 --> 00:57:14.830
to get government out of
the way and change not just

00:57:14.830 --> 00:57:16.660
infrastructure.

00:57:16.660 --> 00:57:20.680
Look, the Chinese
have significant money

00:57:20.680 --> 00:57:24.550
that they have put aside to
do industrial parks in Africa,

00:57:24.550 --> 00:57:26.400
with success in those.

00:57:26.400 --> 00:57:30.130
There are infrastructure hubs
developing out of Australia,

00:57:30.130 --> 00:57:33.520
and all of the private capital
and common infrastructure.

00:57:33.520 --> 00:57:35.840
Nigeria has been talking
about a second major bridge

00:57:35.840 --> 00:57:38.055
for forever.

00:57:38.055 --> 00:57:40.305
Bangladesh, one of the poorest
countries in the world,

00:57:40.305 --> 00:57:44.590
is building several bridges,
an underground tunnel,

00:57:44.590 --> 00:57:45.535
the estuary.

00:57:48.510 --> 00:57:52.090
We need thinking
people to engage

00:57:52.090 --> 00:57:57.550
as private,
non-government actors

00:57:57.550 --> 00:58:01.410
in the international economic
arena for our country.

00:58:01.410 --> 00:58:04.550
And in some ways,
[INAUDIBLE] myself,

00:58:04.550 --> 00:58:07.940
I'm an appointed
ambassador in that area.

00:58:07.940 --> 00:58:11.464
And I hope that this will
make some contribution.

00:58:11.464 --> 00:58:12.380
JULIET EHIMUAN: Right.

